              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2JPNKTO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Kyoto University Research Reactor (KUR) ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The graphite thermal column (TC-Pn) in KUR. The",
                "nominal neutron flux intensity of TC-Pn is 2.84E+11",
                " (n/cm2/sec) at 5 MW power operation. The AUTHORs",
                "confirmed that the TC-Pn was well thermalized on the",
                "basis of Westcott convention using neutron flux",
                "monitors: Au-197, Co-59, and Mo-98. (See Fig. 3 in",
                "the REFERENCE.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "26-FE-58",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.00282
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Sample:    Fe-nat metal foil  5.208+-0.001 mg",
                "Monitor:   Co-nat metal foil  0.640+-0.001 mg",
                "           Mo-nat metal wire 15.378+-0.001 mg",
                "           Au/Al Alloy wire   3.114+-0.001 mg",
                "The sample and the monitors were irradiated",
                "in the TC-Pn for 1 hour under 5-MW power operation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity germanium detector, relative",
                "efficiency of 25%.",
                "The gamma-ray peak efficiencies of the Ge detector",
                "were measured using a Eu-152 source and a mixed source",
                "AM-8140 (Am-241, Cd-109, Co-57, Ce-139, Hg-203, Sn-113,",
                "Cs-137, Co-60 and Y-88) .",
                "The uncertainty in the source radioactivity was 1.5%",
                "for both of the standard sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Based on Westcott convention method.",
                "Because the neutron flux in the TC-Pn is well",
                "thermalized, epithermal component in Westcott",
                "convention method was negligibly small."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction rate of Fe-58 was obtained from",
                "the yield of each decay gamma ray emitted from the",
                "irradiated Fe sample.",
                "The thermal-neutron flux was derived using the reaction",
                "rates and the thermal cross sections of the monitors.",
                "The derived flux was (2.6832+-0.0424)E+10(n/cm2/sec) .",
                "The cross section of Fe-58 was derived from the",
                "reaction rate of Fe-58 and the thermal-neutron flux.",
                "The thermal capture cross sections for monitors and",
                "the g-factors were taken from the REL-REF.",
                "For Mo-98, the thermal capture cross section was taken",
                "from an AUTHOR's unpublished previous measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "AUTHOR's assumed cross section of Mo-98, 0.132+-0.006 b",
                "is close to that given in REL-REF (0.130+-0.06 b) ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-shielding coefficients for thermal neutrons were",
                "calculated from neutron capture cross-sections and",
                "area densities of the sample and the monitors.",
                "The coincidence summing effect was estimated from the",
                "peak-to-total ratios and the peak efficiencies."
              ]
            }
          ],
